CATEGORIES=computers-code;

I had been doing this:

    sudo su -c 'echo AT+MODE=8 > /dev/ttyACM0'

but I think that this is better becasue it spawns one less shell:

    echo AT+MODE=8 | sudo tee /dev/ttyACM0 > /dev/null
